.TH camview 1 "@PROJECT_YEAR@" "@PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
camview \- Raspberry Pi CSI camera preview and capture
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B camview
.RI [ OPTION ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B camview
uses GStreamer's
.B libcamerasrc
to access Raspberry Pi 5 (and compatible) MIPI/CSI cameras, similar in spirit to
.BR cheese (1)
for preview and recording.
.PP
With no capture options it opens a graphical live preview. With
.B \-\-still
or
.B \-\-duration
it runs headless, captures, and exits.
.PP
Preview window keys:
.B P
saves a JPEG into your Pictures directory (or the current directory if XDG is unset);
.B Q
quits the application.
.PP
In preview mode,
.B libcamerasrc
is typically configured for continuous autofocus
.RB ( af\-mode = continuous,
.B af\-speed
fast) unless
.B \-\-no\-autofocus
is given. For still capture, the pipeline waits
.B \-\-af\-settle\-ms
after reaching
.B PLAYING
before pulling one encoded frame.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-still
Capture one still image and exit (headless). Default format is JPEG.
.TP
.BI "\-d " TIME "\fR, " \-\-duration " " TIME
Record H.264 video for the given duration and exit (headless).
.I TIME
accepts a number with optional unit:
.BR ns ", " us ", " ms ", " s ", " min ", " hr
and full words such as
.BR second ", " minute ", " hour
(e.g.
.BR 10s ", " 500ms ", " 2min ", " 1.5hr ).
A bare number is interpreted as seconds.
.TP
.BI "\-f " FORMAT "\fR, " \-\-format " " FORMAT
Still:
.BR jpg ", " jpeg ", or " png .
Video:
.BR mp4 ", " mov ", or " mkv .
Defaults by mode if omitted.
.TP
.BI "\-o " PATH "\fR, " \-\-output " " PATH
Output file. Default:
.B camview_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.ext
in the current working directory.
.TP
.BI "\-i " ID "\fR, " \-\-device " " ID
Select CSI camera by 1-based index (2 is the second camera). When cameras can be listed, requires
.B rpicam\-hello
or
.B libcamera\-hello
for
.B \-\-list\-cameras
unless
.B \-\-camera\-name
is set. If listing is unavailable and only one camera exists, omitting
.B \-i
may still work.
.TP
.BI "\-\-camera\-name " ID
Use the libcamera camera id string directly (overrides
.BR \-i ).
.TP
.BI "\-r " WxH "\fR, " \-\-resolution " " WxH
Scale output with
.BR videoscale ,
e.g.
.BR 1920x1080 .
Omit for the sensor default size.
.TP
.B \-\-framerate \fIN
Video frame rate (default: 30). Applied via a caps filter on raw video before the encoder.
.TP
.B \-\-jpeg\-quality \fIN
JPEG quality 1\(en100 (default: 92). Affects still capture and preview snapshots.
.TP
.B \-\-af\-settle\-ms \fIMS
Milliseconds to wait after the still pipeline reaches
.B PLAYING
before grabbing a frame, so continuous autofocus can settle (default: 1500). Ignored for
.B \-\-no\-autofocus
except for a short fixed delay.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-autofocus
Disable libcamera autofocus controls
.RB ( af\-mode
manual).
.TP
.B \-\-headless
Never open a window. Capture modes are headless by default; this flag is for forcing headless behaviour if extended later.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
More logging (repeat for more detail, via bas logging).
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Less logging.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage and exit successfully.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and license information and exit successfully.
.SH EXAMPLES
Live preview on the default camera:
.PP
.RS
.nf
camview
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use the second CSI camera and record 20 seconds to MP4:
.PP
.RS
.nf
camview \-i 2 \-d 20s \-o out.mp4
.fi
.RE
.PP
High\-resolution PNG still:
.PP
.RS
.nf
camview \-s \-f png \-r 3840x2160 \-o frame.png
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GST_DEBUG
Standard GStreamer debug syntax (e.g.
.BR libcamera:4 ", " *:3 ).
.SH FILES
.I camview_*.jpg
and
.I camview_*.png
default still names in the current directory;
.I camview_*.mp4
(or
.BR .mov ", " .mkv )
for video when
.B \-o
is omitted.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
Runtime plugins include
.B libcamerasrc
(GStreamer libcamera),
.BR gtk4paintablesink ,
image encoders
.RB ( jpegenc ", " pngenc ),
H.264 encoders
.RB ( v4l2h264enc ", " x264enc ", " openh264enc
in preference order), and muxers
.BR mp4mux ", " qtmux ", " matroskamux
as selected by
.BR \-\-format .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid options, resolution of the camera path failed, or capture/pipeline failure.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rpicam\-hello (1),
.BR gst\-launch\-1.0 (1),
.BR cheese (1).
.SH AUTHOR
Written by @PROJECT_AUTHOR@ <@PROJECT_EMAIL@>.
